{ The easiest way to deliver checkmate when you are up by two major pieces (queen or rook) is to force the enemy king to one side of the board using a concept known as the staircase. } { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gf2f5,Gf5a5,Gf5h5] }
1. Qf5 { We start by cutting the king off from a rank or file. The queen prevents the king from advancing to the fifth rank. } 1... Kc6 2. Rg6+ { Using the other major piece, we check the king off the next rank or file. } 2... Kc7 3. Qf7+ { Now the rook stops the king from moving forward, so we use the queen to force the king to the last rank } 3... Kd8 4. Rg8# { Now that the king can't come to the seventh rank, we use the rook to deliver mate.
Same concepts apply with two rooks(or two queens). } *


