{ The plan is to take files/ranks away from the enemy king while pushing it to one side of the board.
Keep your rooks as far from the enemy king as possible.
Keep in mind that this not the fastest way to deliver mate, it's merely the easiest. } { [%csl Ge1][%cal Gg1e1] }
1. Re1+ { Now the king can't cross the e-file since it's controlled by the rook. } 1... Kd3 { Move your g-rook far from the enemy king. } (1... Kf3 2. Rg8) 2. Rg8 (2. Rg7 Kd2) 2... Kd2 { Now your rook on e1 is attacked, move it far away from the enemy king. } 3. Re7 (3. Ree8 { It's true that it's preferred to keep the rooks far away from the enemy king, but the rook now blocks the other rook on g8, and it prevents us from creating the staircase. }) 3... Kd3 { Force the black king to the left. } 4. Rd8+ Kc4 5. Rc7+ Kb5 6. Rb8+ Ka6 { Prepare for the checkmate by moving the rook on c7 to a safe square where it can deliver the checkmate in the next moves. } 7. Rc1 Ka7 { Now move the attacked rook to a safe square far away from the enemy king. } 8. Rb2 Ka6 9. Ra1# *


