{ Start by Trapping the king in a box using the rook, similar to what we did in the queen mate. }
1. Rf5 Kd6 { Bring your king closer to defend and help the rook } 2. Kf3 Kc6 { Continue by bringing the king closer. } 3. Ke4 Kd6 { Move your rook away from the enemy king. } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gf5h5] } 4. Rh5 Kc6 { We need to force the king to the last rank, chase him with your king. } 5. Kd4 Kd6 { Force the king backwards. } 6. Rh6+ Ke7 { Bring your king closer to the rook. } 7. Ke5 (7. Kd5 { Valid alternative move.
We need to get the king closer to the rook. }) 7... Kf7 { Move the rook away from the enemy king. } { [%csl Gb6][%cal Gh6b6] } 8. Rb6 Kg7 { Chase the king to push him to the last rank. } 9. Kf5 Kf7 { Force the king backwards. } 10. Rb7+ Ke8 11. Ke6 Kd8 { Move the rook away from the enemy king. } 12. Rh7 Kc8 { Now chase him with your king until the king oppose each other, which makes the checkmate possible. } 13. Kd6 Kb8 14. Kc6 Ka8 15. Kb6 Kb8 { Deliver the checkmate. } 16. Rh8# *


